{"key":"processedPost-19798351","value":{"id":19798351,"first":19797953,"last":19798948,"when":1396706207,"utime":"04/05/14 04:56 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />It's said that mushrooms can grow in very low light, and certainly a clear lid on a mostly opaque tub seems to provide at least that. <br /></blockquote><br /><br />Yes, it's said all the time by idiots without a clue.&nbsp; Mushrooms grown in low light conditions have low potency, low weight, poor growth and poor pinning performance.&nbsp; <i>P cubensis</i> growing in the wild is almost always in cow pastures in direct sunlight.<br /><br />It's been posted hundreds, if not thousands of time around here that a clear lid on an opaque tub is not sufficient because 80% of the light which reaches the substrate or fruits comes from the sides, not directly above.<br />RR","title":"Re: colour of fruiting chamber"}}